== Archive and Links ==

The [[Beginner's Guide to Tinyfugue]] and then the [[Advanced Guide to Tinyfugue]].

Here are some links to other useful Tinyfugue resources.

* [http://www.druware.com/ Andy Satori's Windows port of Tinyfugue] 
* [http://christianrobinson.name/tf/ Christian Robinson's Tinyfugue Page]
* [http://oj.egbt.org/dmoore/tf/ David Moore's Tinyfugue Page]
* [http://web.archive.org/web/19990508023527/http:/amtgard.com/~marvin/ Marvin Pederson's Site]
* [http://ben.com/MOO/tf-mcp.html (For the MUDders) MCP Support]
* [http://dream.org.uk/dw/tf/ Vashti's Web]
* [http://tnsp.org/~ccr/ggrtf/html/manual.html GR TF Batmud System]
* [http://www.cutery.fi/archive.php?list=tf Backup Archive of the Tinyfugue Mailing List]
* [http://zombiemud.infogami.com/TinyFugue ZombieMUD Macros]
* [http://koti.utanet.fi/~divine/zombie/ More ZombieMUD Macros]
* [http://sourceforge.net/projects/tf-rod-macros/ Worsel's TF macros for RoD]

The last isn't a Tinyfugue link. It's a simple howto on using the screen terminal program. The screen program is very popular with Tinyfugue users.
* [http://www.rackaid.com/resources/linux-screen-tutorial-and-how-to/ screen Howto]</textarea><div class='templatesUsed'>

